---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Data Analysis">
  <div class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8">
        <a href="/learn" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Learn</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-slate-400">Use Cases</span>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Data Analysis</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-violet-500/10 border border-violet-500/20 text-violet-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Use Case
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Data Analysis</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-400">
          Analyze data, generate insights, and create reports
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- Overview -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Overview</h2>
          <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
              AI can help analyze datasets, identify patterns, and generate insights. It works well 
              with structured data, spreadsheets, and even raw text that needs quantification.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-400">
              Provide clear context about your data structure and what insights you're looking for 
              to get the most useful results.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Techniques -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Key Techniques</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-violet-400">Chain-of-Thought</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Request step-by-step analysis for complex datasets</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-cyan-400">Few-Shot</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Show desired output format for consistent analysis</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-400">XML Tags</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Separate data, questions, and output format</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-teal-400">Prompt Chaining</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Break analysis into clean → analyze → report pipeline</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Examples -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Examples</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
              <div class="bg-slate-800 px-6 py-3 border-b border-slate-700">
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-400">Example 1: Trend Analysis</span>
              </div>
              <div class="p-6">
                <div class="mb-4">
                  <span class="text-xs uppercase text-slate-500 mb-1 block">Prompt</span>
                  <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm">
Analyze this sales data and identify:
- Month-over-month growth trends
- Top 3 performing products
- Any seasonal patterns

Data: [sales data table]
Output format: Summary with bullet points and one chart recommendation</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span class="text-xs uppercase text-slate-500 mb-1 block">Output</span>
                  <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg p-4 text-slate-300">
                    <strong>Key Findings:</strong>
                    <br/>• 23% MoM growth (accelerating)
                    <br/>• Top products: Widget Pro, SuperTool, BasicKit
                    <br/>• Q4 shows 40% higher sales (holiday season)
                    <br/><br/>
                    <strong>Chart Recommendation:</strong> Line chart for trends, bar chart for product comparison
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
              <div class="bg-slate-800 px-6 py-3 border-b border-slate-700">
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-400">Example 2: Customer Feedback Analysis</span>
              </div>
              <div class="p-6">
                <div class="mb-4">
                  <span class="text-xs uppercase text-slate-500 mb-1 block">Prompt</span>
                  <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm">
Categorize these customer reviews by sentiment and topic:

1. "Love the product but shipping was terrible"
2. "Best purchase I've made this year"
3. "Good value but needs better instructions"
4. "Customer service was incredibly helpful"

Create a table with: Review, Sentiment, Topics, Action Item</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span class="text-xs uppercase text-slate-500 mb-1 block">Output</span>
                  <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg p-4 text-slate-300">
                    <table class="w-full text-sm">
                      <thead>
                        <tr class="text-left text-slate-400">
                          <th class="pb-2">Review</th>
                          <th class="pb-2">Sentiment</th>
                          <th class="pb-2">Topics</th>
                          <th class="pb-2">Action</th>
                        </tr>
                      </thead>
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td>1</td>
                          <td class="text-amber-400">Mixed</td>
                          <td>Product, Shipping</td>
                          <td>Improve shipping</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>2</td>
                          <td class="text-emerald-400">Positive</td>
                          <td>Overall</td>
                          <td>Use in testimonials</td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Best Practices -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Best Practices</h2>
          <div class="card-gradient rounded-xl p-6">
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="text-violet-400 font-mono">01</span>
                <div>
                  <strong class="text-white">Structure your data clearly</strong>
                  <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Use tables, CSV format, or clear delimiters</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="text-violet-400 font-mono">02</span>
                <div>
                  <strong class="text-white">Ask specific questions</strong>
                  <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Instead of "analyze this," ask "what trends do you see?"</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="text-violet-400 font-mono">03</span>
                <div>
                  <strong class="text-white">Request specific output formats</strong>
                  <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Tables, bullet points, charts - specify what you need</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="text-violet-400 font-mono">04</span>
                <div>
                  <strong class="text-white">Verify critical findings</strong>
                  <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Double-check important insights with follow-up questions</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Navigation -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between pt-8 border-t border-slate-800">
          <a href="/learn/use-cases/writing" class="text-slate-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">
            ← Previous: Writing & Editing
          </a>
          <a href="/learn/use-cases/research" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-xl bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 hover:bg-amber-500/20 transition-colors">
            Next: Research →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
